### Mass and linear momentum

* Mass and inertia

The inertia of a body can be described as its reluctance to start moving, or to change its motion once it has started.

The **mass**\(m\) of a body is the intrinsic property of a body which resists change in motion, i.e. it is a measure of the inertia of a body. The same force, when applied to a body of larger mass will cause a smaller change in motion.

