The law states that whenever body A exerts a force \(\vec{F}_{\text{A\,on\,B}}\) on body B, body B exerts an equal and opposite force \(\vec{F}_{\text{B\,on\,A}}\) on body A.

Mathematically,

\[\left|\vec{F}_{\text{A\,on\,B}}\right|=\left|\vec{F}_{\text{B\,on\,A}}\right| \text{(equal in magnitude)}\]

\[\vec{F}_{\text{A\,on\,B}}=-\vec{F}_{\text{B\,on\,A}}\text{( opposite in direction)}\]

\(\vec{F}_{\text{A\,on\,B}}\) and \(\vec{F}_{\text{B\,on\,A}}\) are known as **action-reaction** pair of forces.

